      "message": "Oof, I didn\u0027t even notice it until now, but even this suggestion makes the case for why I think we should never ever use these types.  The suggestion itself has a bug!\n\nAs written,\n\n   std::aligned_storage\u003csizeof(T), alignof(T)\u003e fStorage[N]\n\nisn\u0027t going to make an array big or aligned enough.  It needs to be\n\n   std::aligned_storage_t\u003csizeof(T), alignof(T)\u003e fStorage[N]\n\nBut still, much simpler and clearer to write \n\n    alignas(T) char fStorage[N*sizeof(T)]",
